0.880 0.600 0.200 rg 44.00 330.61 6.00 18.00 re f
0.840 0.880 0.900 RG 1.10 w 58.00 327.61 m 537.00 327.61 l S
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 58.00 303.58 Td (The broad workflow of OWASP Dependency-Check looks like this:) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 66.00 278.78 Td (1. The tool scans a project, build file, dependency manifest, package archive, or) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 82.00 261.98 Td (directory.) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 66.00 243.18 Td (2. It identifies third-party components by reading manifests, metadata, package) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 82.00 226.38 Td (names, hashes, file names, and archive contents.) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 66.00 207.58 Td (3. It gathers evidence that can map each dependency to standardized identifiers.) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 66.00 188.78 Td (4. It compares those identifiers against vulnerability databases such as CVE data.) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 66.00 169.98 Td (5. It produces a report showing vulnerable dependencies, severity, and references.) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 66.00 151.18 Td (6. Optionally, it fails the build if vulnerabilities exceed a policy threshold.) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 58.00 132.16 Td (The most important internal challenge is identification. Vulnerability matching is) Tj ET
0.130 0.150 0.190 rg BT /F1 11.20 Tf 58.00 115.14 Td (only as good as the dependency identity evidence collected.) Tj ET
0.080 0.330 0.560 rg BT /F2 16.00 Tf 58.00 75.14 Td (Internal Working Mechanism) Tj ET
